doc.previous: Most web pages contain hyperlinks to other related pages and perhaps to downloadable files source documents definitions and other web resources In the underlying HTML a hyperlink looks like a href http example org wiki Main Page Example org a free encyclopedia a
doc.after: Such a collection of useful related resources interconnected via hypertext links is dubbed a web of information Publication on the Internet created what Tim Berners Lee first called the WorldWideWeb in its original CamelCase which was subsequently discarded in November 1990 5
